    <Text>Bermondsey Square is a stylish bespoke 4-star superior hotel located south of the River Thames at the centre point of a revitalised square in the rising area of Bermondsey. The area has a developing scene of galleries, boutiques, bars and restaurants and the square where the hotel is located boasts an independent cinema and contemporary flats surrounding Bermondsey�s famous antiques market. The area surrounding the hotel is rapidly establishing itself as the cooler younger brother to London�s more established neighbourhoods. The City (London�s major business and financial centre) is a short distance away and nearby attractions include Borough Market, Tate Modern, Tower Bridge and the Tower of London. Alfie�s Kitchen is the restaurant and bar at the Bermondsey Square Hotel, with a wine shop and delicatessen attached. The restaurant champions fresh English dishes and there is also a terrace garden which offers alfresco seating. The rooms are modern and light and bright. They feature an iMac TV and Wi-Fi access. Bathrooms have a rain shower and guests can enjoy access to the exclusive members lounge.</Text>
